webpackJsonp([0xd35b5358c125],{9030:function(e,t){e.exports={pathContext:{group:[{node:{fields:{title:"Go Forward! Move Ahead!",date:"31 May 2002",slug:"/2002-05-31-go-forward-move-ahead/",tags:"Y2002"},html:'<p><a href="http://diveintomark.org/">diveintomark</a> has started <a href="http://diveintomark.org/archives/2002/05/31.html#more_on_rss_autodiscovery">championing using a link tag to reference rss feeds</a>, something like this:</p>\n<p><code>&lt;link rel="alternate" type="text/xml" title="XML"<br />\nhref="http://www.papascott.de/xml/index.rdf" /&gt;</code></p>\n<p>Then an aggregator like Radio Userland or Amphetadesk would in theory be able to automatically find the feed. Sounds cool to me.</p>\n<p>(The title of this entry is an obscure lyric reference, but I\'d guess someone like <a href="http://www.vfth.com">Alwin</a> would get it right away.)</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Don't Read This Book, Film At 11",date:"31 May 2002",slug:"/2002-05-31-dont-read-this-book-film-at-11/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"100% Liberal Quaker",date:"01 Jun 2002",slug:"/2002-06-01-100-liberal-quaker/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"Don't Read This Book, Film At 11",date:"31 May 2002",slug:"/2002-05-31-dont-read-this-book-film-at-11/",tags:"Y2002"},html:'<p>Americans will wonder at this... the lead story on last night\'s <a href="http://www.tagesthemen.de">late news</a> was about.... literature. And they went on and on, for at least 10 minutes. In short, the FAZ is refusing to publish the new novel by Martin Walser, "Death of a Critic", because they say it is anti-Semitic and that the <a href="http://www.faz.com/IN/INtemplates/eFAZ/docmain.asp?rub={B1311FFE-FBFB-11D2-B228-00105A9CAF88}&amp;doc={9F018D5D-01B5-46D4-9D65-290CA8EE3CBE}">dead critic is intended to be the real-life FAZ critic Marcel Reich-Ranicki</a>. The publisher could not have orchestrated a better PR campaign.</p>\n<p>I\'m not sure how much the typical German viewer cares about Walser and Reich-Ranicki, but I guess this was better than seeing yet another panic story about the <a href="http://c.moreover.com/click/here.pl?x39453821">Nitrofen scandal</a>.</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Layoffs Update 2",date:"30 May 2002",slug:"/2002-05-30-layoffs-update-2/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Go Forward! Move Ahead!",date:"31 May 2002",slug:"/2002-05-31-go-forward-move-ahead/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"Layoffs Update 2",date:"30 May 2002",slug:"/2002-05-30-layoffs-update-2/",tags:"Y2002"},html:"<p>It's been nearly two weeks since management dropped da bomb, and they still have not given an explanation for their actions, and the topic not even mentioned to stockholders at the annual shareholders meeting this week. There are a lot of rumours and speculation floating around the water cooler. The only thing that seems for sure is that a workers' council <i>(Betriebsrat)</i> will be formed.</p>\n<p>However, a TV will be set up so those of us who are still working can watch  German World Cup matches during working hours.</p>"},next:{fields:{title:"BlogMap",date:"30 May 2002",slug:"/2002-05-30-blogmap/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Don't Read This Book, Film At 11",date:"31 May 2002",slug:"/2002-05-31-dont-read-this-book-film-at-11/"}}}],pathPrefix:"",first:!1,last:!1,index:891,pageCount:1101}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---891-af8cafbe4711dbaaa99f.js.map